            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> June 5615</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I received yours of <date>31<hi rend="sup">st</hi></date> ult. last
                week with<lb/> the Occidents and regret to learn from it you had not been quite<lb/>
                well since your return to <placeName>Phila.</placeName> I presume however, you<lb/>
                require no one to point out to you the inutility of permitting<lb/> yourself to be
                annoyed because all things go not right. As<lb/> for the fictional convention &amp;
                the doings of our ultra reformers<lb/> (permit me to say you attach as I think too
                much importance<lb/> to them. By showing the extreme ugliness of their <hi
                    rend="underline">deformities</hi><lb/> if I may so say we can better serve the
                cause of historical<lb/> Judaism than by creating into heroes a few men who
                have<lb/> more philosophy than religion. The talent &amp; activity of these<lb/>
                ultras cannot but be admired, and movement and life<lb/> are always better than
                drowsiness &amp; stagnation. Perhaps<lb/> if it were not for the doings of some of
                these mischievous<lb/> demagogues a long <add>תרדמה</add> would fall upon the
                people<lb/>—awaking from which we should find the fabric of Judaism<lb/> had so
                suffered that most laborious efforts persevered<lb/> in for many years must be
                resorted to, to restore it<lb/> to its pristine excellence.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am greatly obliged to you for advertising<lb/> my proposals to
                publish school-books but will not further<lb/> avail myself of your kindness for the
                present because<lb/> for the present I abandon the idea of publication.<lb/>
                Templo's Grammar I would have published as I intended</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>(as I before wrote you) so soon as you had returned; because you<lb/> wrote me in
                    <date>October</date> or <date>November</date> “it would not be a killing<lb/>
                thing” &amp; you “would not mind lending a hand so that But,<lb/> perhaps I have to
                thank you that I have not embarked in<lb/> a lap to both. Please under the
                circumstances discontinue<lb/> the advertisement.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Now that I see <persName>Mende's</persName> Sermon, I did not see
                the no of the Chron<add>?</add> containing it. I don't know<lb/> why
                    <persName>Wise</persName> should <add>?</add> out so lustily “plagiarism.”
                An<lb/> eulogy of mine of “Vaterland” given before a crowded audience<lb/> on
                Humiliation Day (I sent you a paper did you receive it?)<lb/> was inserted almost
                word for word as the lucubrations<lb/> of one of our “head-hitters” a couple of days
                after. There<lb/> was no mistaking it, but I certainly did not think<lb/> of calling
                him to account. Mais apropas des battes—<lb/> I am sorry you appearing as a
                correspondent of the Israelite<lb/> you <add>?</add>. Will you please do me a favor,
                and let<lb/> one know “by return of post” what induced you<lb/> to write this. I do
                not recollect having contributed<lb/> anything to the Israelite and will gladly pay
                10 cents<lb/> to have my memory respected, if I have written and<lb/> forgotten. I
                am anxious to hear from you on this<lb/> subject. I would write however for any
                paper if I<lb/> thought I could thereby advance the cause I desire to serve<lb/>
                always provided I was fairly &amp; properly treated.<lb/> I will even contribute
                (when so <hi rend="underline">urged</hi>)<lb/> to baby publications <add>?</add>
                magazines which <add>?</add><lb/> to spring up but which I guess not more, if as
                much<lb/> as the older ones will flourish. I have not seen<lb/>
                <persName>Wises</persName> article <add>בכבע נראה לי ציצית</add>—I must close
                    <add>?</add>sting you <add>כל טוב</add></p>
            <p>I will submit your circular.    </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">I am yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
